Generic single-database configuration.

This directory contains the Alembic migration system for the Ontario Driving School Manager.

The migration system is used to:
- Track database schema changes
- Apply versioned migrations
- Handle database upgrades and downgrades

Key files:
- alembic.ini: Main configuration file
- env.py: Environment configuration
- script.py.mako: Migration template
- versions/: Directory containing migration files

Migration files are named with a sequential number and description:
001_initial_schema.py
002_add_compliance_tables.py
003_add_toronto_zones.py
004_add_cancellation_tracking.py
005_add_insurance_medical.py
006_add_mto_export_tracking.py
007_add_gps_retention_triggers.py
008_add_version_tracking.py

To run migrations:
1. Upgrade to latest: alembic upgrade head
2. Downgrade one version: alembic downgrade -1
3. Create new migration: alembic revision -m "description"

For more information, see the Alembic documentation:
https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/ 